Webster
1. {Webster's Dictionary}.
2. A {World-Wide Web} {browser} for the {Acorn} {Archimedes}. The {HTML} files may reside locally or be retrieved using a "fetcher". An {HTTP} fetcher for use with {KA9Q} is supplied.
Version: 0.05.

Definition.WordDefinition: Webster \Web"ster\, n. [AS. webbestre. See {Web}, {Weave}, and {-ster}.] A weaver; originally, a female weaver. [Obs.] --Brathwait. [1913 Webster]

Webster n 1: English playwright (1580-1625) [syn: {John Webster}] 2: United States politician and orator (1782-1817) [syn: {Daniel Webster}] 3: United States lexicographer (1758-1843) [syn: {Noah Webster}]
